quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  33,21,"You have indeed in the Prophet of God a good example for those of you who look to God and the Last Day, and remember God always"
  33,22,"When the believers saw the confederates, they said, \"This is what God and His Messenger have promised us. Surely the promise of God and His Messenger has come true.\" It served to increase them in faith and submission"
  33,23,"Among the believers there are men who have been true to the pledge they made with God. Among them are such as have fulfilled their vow, and some who [still] wait, without having changed [their resolve] in the least"
  33,24,"God will surely reward the truthful for their truthfulness and punish the hypocrites, if He so wishes, or He may accept their repentance, for God is forgiving and merciful"
  33,25,"God turned back those who denied the truth in their rage, without their having gained any advantage. God was enough to [protect] the believers in battle. God is strong and all-powerful"
  33,26,He brought down from their strongholds those People of the Book who supported the aggressors and filled their hearts with terror. Some of them you killed and others you took captive
  33,27,"He made you heirs to their lands, and their houses, and their possessions and lands on which you had not set foot before. God has power over all things"